19/08/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- Besim Beqja, chief co-ordinator of the Stability Pact for Kosovo, urged the Albanian Parliament on Monday (18 Monday) to adopt the free trade accord between Albania and Kosovo. During an official visit to Tirana, Beqja called the adoption the first step towards making Kosovo a key part of the regional integration process. Meeting with Deputy Foreign Minister Luan Hajdaraga, who also serves as Albania's Co-ordinator of the Stability Pact, Beqja said he appreciated Tirana's role in defining Kosovo's place in the Balkans. (ATA, BBC - 18/08/03)
